The forum, which is already over subscribed from 1 500 to more than 3 000 delegates from across the globe will be focusing on all the 17 Sustainable Development Goals and how Africa is fairing or lagging behind.

Climate change will be on the agenda and as such the United Nations Deputy Secretary General Amina Mahomed is already in Zimbabwe assessing some of the challenges the country is facing. More from our Correspondent based in Harare, Zimbabwe, Simon Muchemwa...

